comments: CHB = beyond hold time, should overrule 0
GDM = data missing or sample never collected; if GDM is mistake then data's okay based on 0; if GDM is correct it's an NA anyway
SBL = below detection limit, but -3 indicates other reasons for rejecting
A = above detection limits; mostly seems accidental
N = negative value; though keep because adjusted to detection limit anyway; Melissa recomends excluding
CLE = sample collected earlier/later than scheduled
CUS = lab analysis from unpreserved sample
SCB = calculated with a value below the mdl
